Shembe church leaders were in Inanda assisting flood victims. eNCA senior reporter Siphamandla Goge reports. Courtesy #DSTV403 DURBAN - The country commemorates Freedom Day in the wake of catastrophic floods in KwaZulu-Natal, where relief efforts are ongoing. The province cancelled all major events as it tries to pick up the pieces from this month's storms. Shembe church leaders were in Inanda on Wednesday assisting flood victims. eNCA senior reporter Siphamandla Goge shares more details in the video above.